headline: How Recent Developments Are Reshaping the Target Investment Story
summary: The consensus analyst price target for Target has slipped slightly, moving from $101.36 to $100.70 per share. Expectations for the company’s near-term value have been gently revised downward. This adjustment follows recent analysis reflecting both optimism about management changes and operational improvements, as well as continued uncertainty stemming from ongoing challenges. Stay tuned to learn how you can keep track of evolving analyst sentiment and key factors shaping Target’s outlook...

headline: Retailers Are Talking Affordable Turkey as the Holiday Season Begins
summary: With shoppers looking for deals, the big retailers are rolling out Thanksgiving meals for the lowest price. It’s a tricky balancing act between margins and market share.

headline: Nvidia earnings, FOMC minutes, Sept. jobs report: What to Watch
summary: Market Domination Overtime host Myles Udland previews several of the biggest stories to come throughout next week, including quarterly earnings results from major companies like Nvidia (NVDA), Home Depot (HD), Target (TGT), and Walmart (WMT); the latest round of commentary from top Federal Reserve officials alongside the minutes from the central bank's October FOMC meeting; and the release of the long-awaited September jobs report scheduled for Thursday, November 20. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Market Domination Overtime.
